<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Newcastle survived a scare at League Two Newport County to reach the Carabao Cup quarter-finals on Wednesday night.</p>

<p>The Welsh side grabbed a shock lead in the fifth minute when Tristan Abrahams' tame effort was fumbled into the net by Newcastle's stand-in goalkeeper Mark Gillespie.</p>

<p>Jonjo Shelvey scored an 87th minute equaliser and the visitors prevailed in a penalty shootout.</p>

